  "prompt": "What is the salary of various elected representatives in India?",
  "response": "The salaries of elected representatives in India, including Members of Parliament (MPs), Members of Legislative Assemblies (MLAs), and other officials, are determined by the government and revised periodically. As of 2023, here are the current salary structures for various elected representatives in India:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Members of Parliament (MPs):**\n- **Basic Salary**: \u20b91,00,000 per month.\n- **Allowances**:\n  - Constituency Allowance: \u20b970,000 per month.\n  - Office Expenses Allowance: \u20b960,000 per month.\n- **Total**: \u20b92,30,000 per month.  \nAdditionally, MPs receive perks like travel allowances, housing, and medical facilities.\n\n---\n\n### **2. President of India:**\n- **Salary**: \u20b95,00,000 per month (fixed).  \nThe President also receives free accommodation, medical facilities, and other allowances.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Vice President of India:**\n- **Salary**: \u20b94,00,000 per month (fixed).  \nThe Vice President also receives allowances and facilities similar to those of the President.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Prime Minister of India:**\n- The Prime Minister does not have a specific salary separate from that of an MP.  \nThe PM receives the same salary and allowances as an MP, along with additional perks like official residence, travel, and security.\n\n---\n\n### **5. State Chief Ministers:**\n- The salary of Chief Ministers varies by state but typically ranges from **\u20b91,50,000 to \u20b93,00,000 per month**, depending on the state's legislative decisions.  \nThey also receive allowances, housing, and other benefits.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Members of Legislative Assemblies (MLAs) and Councils (MLCs):**\n- Salaries vary by state. On average:\n  - Basic Salary: \u20b925,000 to \u20b91,50,000 per month.\n  - Allowances: For constituency, travel, and office expenses.  \nFor example:\n  - Delhi: \u20b92,10,000 per month (including allowances).\n  - Maharashtra: \u20b92,30,000 per month (including allowances).\n  - Uttar Pradesh: \u20b91,87,000 per month (including allowances).\n\n---\n\n### **7. MLAs in Union Territories** (e.g., Delhi, Puducherry):  \nSalaries are determined by the central government.  \nFor example, in Delhi:  \n- Basic Salary: \u20b930,000 per month.\n- Allowances: \u20b91,80,000 per month.\n- Total: \u20b92,10,000 per month.\n\n---\n\nThese salaries and allowances are periodically revised by the respective governments (central or state) based on recommendations from committees or legislative decisions.",
